text: Pascale Got (born April 1, 1961 in Royan, Charente-Maritime) was a member of the National Assembly of France. She represented Gironde's 5th constituency from 2007 to 2017, as a member of the Socialist Party and the Socialiste, radical, citoyen et divers gauche parliamentary group. ==References== Category:1961 births Category:Living people Category:People from Royan Category:Socialist Party (France) politicians Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France) Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:21st-century French women politicians
